Transcription.Text: Here we stopped, as in fine weather we always stopped. Then here was Nice, and the old holiday sea, blue as a new school exercise book. The same old Nice, creamy, vulgar, out of time, bitter-sweet with the ghosts of dead monarchs and brilliant prostitutes, edging past grubby grandeur to the old sleeping port.
